# Install as /etc/agent-bridge/rollout-bootstrap.conf with root:root ownership and mode 0600.
# This is a fixed allowlist, not a shell file. Values cannot contain newlines.
# Separate from rollout.conf: a path here does not authorize ordinary
# migration, and a path in rollout.conf's `database=` allowlist does not
# authorize bootstrap. Only list role/path pairs that are genuinely expected
# to be missing (a new database role not yet created), never an existing
# production database. Each entry is role:absolute-path — role must be one
# of shared, discord, health, interactive, worker (the five canonical roles
# in docs/roadmap/issue-135-phase4c-migration-ownership.md §4). The path
# alone does not authorize bootstrap; the exact (role, path) pair must match.
project_dir=/home/content-crawler/agent-bridge
runtime_user=content-crawler
node_bin=/home/content-crawler/.nvm/versions/node/v24.15.0/bin/node
# bootstrap_role=worker:/home/content-crawler/runtime/agent-bridge/some-new-role/bridge.sqlite
